        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;600;700&family=Merriweather:wght@400;700&display=swap');
        
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: #fcfcfc; /* Warm very light gray/off-white */
            color: #292524; /* Stone 800 */
        }
        
        h1, h2, h3, h4 {
            font-family: 'Merriweather', serif;
        }

        /* Chart Container Requirements */
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px; /* Prevent excessive width */
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 320px; /* Base height */
            max-height: 400px;
        }

        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 380px; /* Slightly taller on desktop */
            }
        }

        /* Interactive Elements */
        .module-card {
            transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-left: 4px solid transparent;
        }
        .module-card:hover {
            transform: translateX(4px);
            background-color: #f5f5f4; /* Stone 100 */
            border-left-color: #0d9488; /* Teal 600 */
        }
        .module-card.active {
            background-color: #f0fdfa; /* Teal 50 */
            border-left-color: #0f766e; /* Teal 700 */
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 2px 4px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
        }

        /* Custom Scrollbar for content area */
        .scrollable-content::-webkit-scrollbar {
            width: 6px;
        }
        .scrollable-content::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
            background: #f5f5f4;
        }
        .scrollable-content::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
            background: #d6d3d1;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        .scrollable-content::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
            background: #a8a29e;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="antialiased min-h-screen flex flex-col">

    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals with Teal and Amber accents to represent calm, academic rigor, and humanism. Background: Stone-50, Text: Stone-800, Accents: Teal-600 (Primary), Amber-600 (Secondary/Highlights). -->

    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA utilizes a "Dashboard/Learning Hub" architecture. It replaces the linear reading experience of a traditional syllabus with an interactive, side-by-side exploration layout. 
    1. A header introduces the course context.
    2. The main body is split: a navigation panel on the left listing the 6 units, and a dynamic content display area on the right. This allows users to jump between topics while maintaining the overall context of the curriculum.
    3. Below the curriculum explorer, a dedicated section visualizes the practical assessment (Role Play Rubrics) using charts to clearly communicate expectations visually, breaking up textual density. -->

    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
    1. Syllabus Units -> Goal: Organize & Explore -> Method: Interactive Sidebar & Dynamic Detail Pane -> Interaction: Click module to load details. -> Justification: Facilitates non-linear exploration and reduces cognitive load compared to a long scroll. -> Method: Vanilla JS + Tailwind.
    2. Role Play Rubric -> Goal: Inform on Assessment Criteria -> Method: Radar Chart -> Interaction: Hover for tooltips. -> Justification: A radar chart perfectly illustrates the necessary balance of multiple skill dimensions (Empathy, Communication, Ethics, Resolution) expected in practical assessments. -> Library: Chart.js (NO SVG).
    3. Cultural Evolution Concept -> Goal: Change/Process -> Method: Horizontal Bar/Timeline Chart -> Interaction: Hover details. -> Justification: Visually represents the shift from primitive to post-modern, providing a conceptual anchor for Unit 1. -> Library: Chart.js.
    4. Visual cues -> Goal: Decorate/Indicate -> Method: Unicode Emojis -> Justification: Strictly adheres to NO SVG/Mermaid rule while maintaining a modern UI feel. -->

    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. All visual elements are CSS, Unicode, or Canvas-based. -->

